<h2 id="for-what">For what?</h2>
<p>There is no arguing that Microsoft has a firm grip on infrastructures inside many corporations, at least when it comes to IDPs and other cloud infrastructures.</p>
<p>One of the systems they use is &ldquo;Privileged Identity Management.&rdquo; I will not attempt to describe it here. Just know that many admins need to use it very, very often to work.</p>
<p>The UI/UX on the Entra/Azure portal is, however, very infuriating in many ways. If you know, you know.</p>
<h2 id="for-quick-access">For quick access</h2>
<figure><img src="https://macowners.club/images/raycast-epim-1.png" width="800px">
</figure>

<p>Being a macOS user and loving Raycast, I could not resist bringing the tedious task to the tip of my fingers.</p>
<p>The solution is a Raycast extension to activate eligible roles. A little bonus is the ability to see activated assignments and their duration.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Epim - Activate Entra Role via PIM with Graph</p>
</blockquote>
<dl>
<dt>Gitlab Repo</dt>
<dd><a href="https://gitlab.com/aimebertrand/raycast-epim">raycast-epim</a></dd>
<dt>PR for the Raycast Extension</dt>
<dd><a href="https://github.com/raycast/extensions/pull/17888">Add epim extension #17888</a></dd>
</dl>
<p><del>The PR has not been merged yet, but fingers are crossed.</del></p>
